WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:53.300 --> 00:01:58.640
Island of New Beginnings

3
00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:00.470
Hurry...

4
00:02:00.470 --> 00:02:02.210
Hurry and apologize already!

5
00:02:02.750 --> 00:02:05.640
Does this guy have a death wish?

6
00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:13.730
I think you're starting to see
how reckless you were!

7
00:02:14.650 --> 00:02:19.420
That's why you're too scared to even talk!

8
00:02:19.420 --> 00:02:20.720
Just moments ago,

9
00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:27.030
a man with a long nose and a woman
with long hair crossed us,

10
00:02:27.030 --> 00:02:30.400
so our captain is in a bad mood.

11
00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:31.840
Apologize quickly.

12
00:02:32.550 --> 00:02:34.240
Prostrate yourself!

13
00:02:34.240 --> 00:02:39.750
Otherwise, this one little mistake
will end up costing your life.

14
00:02:39.750 --> 00:02:43.880
Our captain has an itchy trigger finger.

15
00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:50.450
Kneel on the ground already!
This guy is Straw Hat Luffy!

16
00:02:50.450 --> 00:02:53.270
Does he want to get killed? Apologize!

17
00:02:53.270 --> 00:02:55.430
I'm really sorry!

18
00:02:55.430 --> 00:02:57.490
I need to get going.

19
00:02:58.860 --> 00:03:01.300
– What's wrong with him?!
– What's wrong with him?!

20
00:03:06.830 --> 00:03:08.410
Okay!

21
00:03:08.980 --> 00:03:11.340
That does it!

22
00:03:43.370 --> 00:03:45.040
– What?!
– What?!

23
00:03:45.040 --> 00:03:46.240
What the...?!

24
00:03:50.190 --> 00:03:53.580
Hey, did he do something just now?

25
00:03:58.970 --> 00:04:02.160
I'd like to head out on a fishing trip.

26
00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:04.030
Well, you can't, crap for brains!

27
00:04:04.030 --> 00:04:08.970
Why not?! And why should I listen to you?!

28
00:04:08.970 --> 00:04:13.120
Do you think I'm walking
with you because I want to?!

29
00:04:13.120 --> 00:04:17.410
You'll cause me more trouble
if you go wandering off again!

30
00:04:17.410 --> 00:04:18.640
You muddled moss ball!

31
00:04:18.640 --> 00:04:23.010
Everyone will be here soon,
so just follow me to the ship!

32
00:04:26.350 --> 00:04:28.050
Good grief.

33
00:04:29.270 --> 00:04:33.190
What's with the seventh
trying to boss around the first?

34
00:04:33.190 --> 00:04:36.330
Why are you ranking us
in the order we got here?!

35
00:04:36.330 --> 00:04:40.900
You being the first was a fluke,
so don't let it go to your head!

36
00:04:40.900 --> 00:04:44.840
Yeah, my bad... number seven.

37
00:04:44.840 --> 00:04:46.970
Alright, you asked for it!

38
00:04:47.970 --> 00:04:50.670
I trained my legs in hell for two years!

39
00:04:51.240 --> 00:04:54.610
Bring it on! I'll cut you clean in half!

40
00:05:00.220 --> 00:05:01.730
Captain...!

41
00:05:01.730 --> 00:05:02.890
Captain Luffy!

42
00:05:04.110 --> 00:05:05.490
Damn!

43
00:05:06.420 --> 00:05:07.930
Luffy!

44
00:05:09.190 --> 00:05:11.400
I missed you guys!

45
00:05:11.400 --> 00:05:12.600
Hey!

46
00:05:12.600 --> 00:05:14.800
Luffy!

47
00:05:13.900 --> 00:05:14.800
What?

48
00:05:15.460 --> 00:05:16.970
Franky!

49
00:05:16.420 --> 00:05:16.970
Huh?

50
00:05:16.970 --> 00:05:19.070
Nami!

51
00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:19.070
Huh?!

52
00:05:21.840 --> 00:05:25.110
S... Sogeking?!

53
00:05:24.560 --> 00:05:25.110
Hm?

54
00:05:25.110 --> 00:05:27.410
Cool!

55
00:05:27.410 --> 00:05:30.710
You guys have changed in the last two years!

56
00:05:30.710 --> 00:05:32.980
I bet you got stronger!

57
00:05:34.180 --> 00:05:36.300
It's the Straw Hats.

58
00:05:36.300 --> 00:05:38.940
What are they doing on the street?

59
00:05:38.940 --> 00:05:40.390
Well, what happened was...

60
00:05:40.390 --> 00:05:45.330
Avoid eye contact.
You don't want to fight them.

61
00:05:46.670 --> 00:05:48.460
D-Dammit!

62
00:05:48.460 --> 00:05:50.710
What happened to you?

63
00:05:51.300 --> 00:05:52.470
I don't know!

64
00:05:53.270 --> 00:05:55.710
I felt chills all over my body!

65
00:05:57.710 --> 00:05:59.770
What kind of trick did he pull?

66
00:06:00.580 --> 00:06:04.250
Oh, yeah! We have another problem.

67
00:06:04.250 --> 00:06:05.750
The thing is, Cocoa got–

68
00:06:05.750 --> 00:06:07.320
No, I mean...

69
00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:09.260
Nico Robin got...

70
00:06:09.260 --> 00:06:10.550
What was that, Zoro?!

71
00:06:10.550 --> 00:06:13.050
Nico Robin got abducted?!

72
00:06:13.050 --> 00:06:16.430
I'm sorry. It happened right before our eyes.

73
00:06:16.430 --> 00:06:19.000
Yeah, that's right! This is serious, Luffy!

74
00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:22.530
She could have been kidnapped,
just like Camie was!

75
00:06:22.530 --> 00:06:23.970
Wha...?

76
00:06:25.210 --> 00:06:26.500
Who did it?

77
00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:29.720
Uh... I haven't the foggiest.

78
00:06:29.720 --> 00:06:30.840
Captain,

79
00:06:30.840 --> 00:06:37.150
I think the people who are after
the real Robin took Cocoa by mistake.

80
00:06:37.150 --> 00:06:38.450
That's possible.

81
00:06:39.460 --> 00:06:44.320
She looked so much like the real Robin...
That did not go in our favor.

82
00:06:44.960 --> 00:06:47.390
Hey, stop whispering!

83
00:06:47.390 --> 00:06:48.330
What?

84
00:06:49.990 --> 00:06:52.230
Well, not much we can do now.

85
00:06:52.230 --> 00:06:54.000
That's her fate.

86
00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:54.770
– What?!
– What?!

87
00:06:54.770 --> 00:06:55.730
O-Okay, Captain.

88
00:06:55.730 --> 00:06:56.600
What?!

89
00:06:56.600 --> 00:06:59.840
Hey, Luffy! Robin has been abducted!

90
00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:04.550
And what the hell is this creature?

91
00:07:05.610 --> 00:07:07.890
Is that supposed to be a joke?!

92
00:07:07.890 --> 00:07:10.580
Now's not the time to say such things!

93
00:07:10.580 --> 00:07:13.320
How can he speak? Is he a stuffed animal?

94
00:07:13.320 --> 00:07:15.150
Take it back, Luffy!

95
00:07:15.150 --> 00:07:16.090
Shut up!

96
00:07:20.190 --> 00:07:21.700
Forget about that thing!

97
00:07:21.700 --> 00:07:27.900
Just meet at Grove 46 with
the hundred recruits we found here!

98
00:07:28.430 --> 00:07:29.930
That long-nosed man...

99
00:07:30.440 --> 00:07:31.900
That orange-haired woman...

100
00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:35.230
That brat with the cloak and giant backpack...

101
00:07:36.270 --> 00:07:38.840
Find those three...

102
00:07:38.840 --> 00:07:43.650
and make them regret
crossing Straw Hat Luffy!

103
00:07:43.650 --> 00:07:45.050
– Oh! Roger!
– Oh! Roger!

104
00:07:45.050 --> 00:07:48.690
Let's do our best not to kill them
before bringing them here.

105
00:07:48.690 --> 00:07:52.890
Let's use this opportunity
to show them we mean business!

106
00:07:52.890 --> 00:07:54.190
Okay, let's go!

107
00:07:54.190 --> 00:07:56.630
Wait a minute, you guys!

108
00:07:56.630 --> 00:08:00.030
Have these last two years
warped your personalities so much?

109
00:08:00.030 --> 00:08:01.430
Luffy?!

110
00:08:01.430 --> 00:08:05.200
I... I... feel so sad...

111
00:08:05.200 --> 00:08:07.240
All I can do is cry!

112
00:08:07.900 --> 00:08:10.310
Again, what is this creature?

113
00:08:10.310 --> 00:08:14.370
What about Robin? Why don't
you guys say something?!

114
00:08:14.370 --> 00:08:16.960
Huh? How can he talk?

115
00:08:16.960 --> 00:08:19.380
Toys today are pretty advanced!

116
00:08:19.380 --> 00:08:23.420
Dammit! You guys aren't
at all who I thought you were!

117
00:08:23.420 --> 00:08:27.990
I'll go save her all on my own!

118
00:08:31.330 --> 00:08:34.770
Wait for me, Robin!

119
00:08:37.230 --> 00:08:38.370
What happened?

120
00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:40.630
Is there some infighting?

121
00:08:40.630 --> 00:08:41.510
It's them...

122
00:08:42.410 --> 00:08:44.270
No doubt about it.

123
00:08:44.270 --> 00:08:48.900
The Straw Hat Pirates may look
radically different from two years ago,

124
00:08:49.870 --> 00:08:52.350
but no one else has a weird pet like that!

125
00:08:52.920 --> 00:08:54.080
They're...

126
00:08:55.350 --> 00:08:56.950
the Straw Hats!

127
00:08:56.950 --> 00:08:58.560
They're alive!

128
00:08:59.760 --> 00:09:05.530
This is Grove 47. We've positively identified
the pirate group as the Straw Hats!

129
00:09:08.930 --> 00:09:12.670
Marine Station, Grove 66

130
00:09:09.710 --> 00:09:16.810
Apparently, all the pirates that Straw Hat recruited
from this island are assembling at Grove 46!

131
00:09:16.810 --> 00:09:19.640
Understood! Roger that!

132
00:09:19.640 --> 00:09:22.580
Go and evacuate the civilians immediately!

133
00:09:22.590 --> 00:09:23.480
Roger that!

134
00:09:23.480 --> 00:09:27.660
Pirates are gathering at Grove 46!

135
00:09:27.660 --> 00:09:31.150
The target is the Straw Hats!
We're raiding the lawless area!

136
00:09:31.150 --> 00:09:32.990
Get ready for action!

137
00:09:32.990 --> 00:09:37.760
Close in on them from
Groves 40, 42, and 44!

138
00:09:37.760 --> 00:09:40.100
Backup from G-1 is on the way!

139
00:09:47.350 --> 00:09:49.710
S-Sentomaru, sir!

140
00:09:50.140 --> 00:09:51.810
I'll lead the charge!

141
00:09:52.350 --> 00:09:56.110
PX-5 and PX-7 will come with me!

142
00:09:56.110 --> 00:09:59.620
Wha...? You're deploying the pacifista?!

143
00:09:59.620 --> 00:10:01.320
Of course!

144
00:10:03.250 --> 00:10:06.560
All of you are underestimating the Straw Hats!

145
00:10:08.070 --> 00:10:10.600
It's been two years since the war now.

146
00:10:10.600 --> 00:10:12.900
They must have gotten stronger!

147
00:10:13.430 --> 00:10:17.230
They're nothing like the rookies
that normally come to this island!

148
00:10:20.510 --> 00:10:21.630
The meaning behind...

149
00:10:23.070 --> 00:10:27.540
Warlord Kuma's actions from
two years ago remain a mystery.

150
00:10:30.630 --> 00:10:35.390
However, I observed how he behaved
after losing his personality,

151
00:10:35.390 --> 00:10:41.860
leading me to conclude that the Straw Hats
would reunite here one day!

152
00:10:42.190 --> 00:10:44.030
Let's go!

153
00:10:58.910 --> 00:11:00.950
Robin!

154
00:10:58.980 --> 00:11:05.620
Grove 35
Sabaody Archipelago

155
00:11:02.870 --> 00:11:05.620
Where did they take her?!

156
00:11:06.520 --> 00:11:11.890
Damn! Damn! Damn! Damn!

157
00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:15.130
What happened to everybody?!

158
00:11:16.820 --> 00:11:22.670
Luffy, Zoro, Nami, Sanji, Franky...

159
00:11:22.670 --> 00:11:25.650
They used to be so compassionate!

160
00:11:26.400 --> 00:11:29.640
Robin gets abducted and
he says "leave it at that"?

161
00:11:31.740 --> 00:11:34.220
It's too cruel!

162
00:11:34.220 --> 00:11:38.010
Just... what have I been working toward
for the past two years?!

163
00:11:39.530 --> 00:11:41.120
And for whom?!

164
00:11:44.580 --> 00:11:46.490
Hey, Chopper!

165
00:11:46.490 --> 00:11:47.860
Hey!

166
00:11:51.040 --> 00:11:52.230
Over here!

167
00:11:53.610 --> 00:11:55.630
I knew it was Chopper!

168
00:11:59.200 --> 00:12:00.960
Usopp!

169
00:12:00.960 --> 00:12:04.100
Oh man, you got so big!

170
00:12:04.100 --> 00:12:06.940
I'll bet you're a comfy ride now!

171
00:12:06.940 --> 00:12:08.280
You been doin' alright?

172
00:12:08.280 --> 00:12:09.150
Uh-huh!

173
00:12:09.150 --> 00:12:13.280
He's right! You're much softer than before!

174
00:12:13.280 --> 00:12:14.650
Huh?

175
00:12:14.650 --> 00:12:16.790
It's been a long time, Chopper!

176
00:12:17.820 --> 00:12:18.660
Oh?

177
00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:22.070
Nami?

178
00:12:22.070 --> 00:12:22.930
That's me.

179
00:12:24.590 --> 00:12:25.700
Oh, yeah!

180
00:12:26.140 --> 00:12:29.770
I'm glad to see you guys,
but we're running out of time!

181
00:12:29.770 --> 00:12:31.970
Robin's in trouble!

182
00:12:37.310 --> 00:12:39.940
Huh? You mean they're impostors?

183
00:12:40.360 --> 00:12:42.570
That's why there are two Namis?

184
00:12:43.350 --> 00:12:44.650
Oh, please!

185
00:12:45.530 --> 00:12:49.290
Robin's eluded the government
for twenty years!

186
00:12:49.290 --> 00:12:53.360
It's unthinkable that she could get
stuffed into a sack and taken so easily.

187
00:12:53.880 --> 00:12:54.910
I see!

188
00:12:54.910 --> 00:12:57.630
I thought there was something wrong...

189
00:12:57.630 --> 00:12:59.490
She didn't even smell familiar!

190
00:13:01.500 --> 00:13:03.760
Oh, I'm pissed off now!

191
00:13:03.760 --> 00:13:07.370
Who do they think they are, posing as us?!

192
00:13:07.370 --> 00:13:10.800
How dare they imitate us!

193
00:13:10.800 --> 00:13:12.880
It's almost as if we're...

194
00:13:12.880 --> 00:13:14.810
as if... as if...

195
00:13:14.810 --> 00:13:19.310
as if we're the real deal, those jerks!

196
00:13:19.310 --> 00:13:21.570
What are you so happy about?

197
00:13:21.570 --> 00:13:26.860
Well, I guess having impersonators was bound
to happen, what with our captain's fame.

198
00:13:28.270 --> 00:13:30.120
How should I sign my autograph?

199
00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:32.460
Oh! I've already settled on mine!

200
00:13:32.460 --> 00:13:36.770
You get that this isn't
the good kind of fame, right?

201
00:13:42.070 --> 00:13:45.020
Hey, Chopper!

202
00:13:46.150 --> 00:13:47.810
Chopper!

203
00:13:47.810 --> 00:13:53.220
Man! We lucked into the real
Straw Hats' pet, but we already lost it!

204
00:13:54.550 --> 00:13:56.090
Ouch! My side!

205
00:13:56.220 --> 00:13:58.020
What did you say?!

206
00:13:58.020 --> 00:14:02.490
That strange creature used to be
with the real Straw Hats?!

207
00:14:02.950 --> 00:14:04.830
Why didn't you say so earlier?

208
00:14:04.830 --> 00:14:06.820
Go and bring him back here!

209
00:14:06.820 --> 00:14:08.230
– What?!
– What?!

210
00:14:08.300 --> 00:14:12.440
We'll never find him if we
don't know where to look!

211
00:14:12.440 --> 00:14:16.060
We've completely lost him!
Sabaody Archipelago is too big!

212
00:14:16.060 --> 00:14:17.940
Ouch! My side! It hurts!

213
00:14:21.410 --> 00:14:24.830
We can't run anymore!
Let's... Let's just walk.

214
00:14:26.180 --> 00:14:30.620
Hancock was right. I need this mustache.

215
00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:32.720
She told me to stay outta trouble.

216
00:14:35.970 --> 00:14:37.170
Hey! Look!

217
00:14:37.170 --> 00:14:40.000
Is that the caped backpack brat
the Captain mentioned?

218
00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:43.570
You call that a brat?
More like a cheerful old man.

219
00:14:45.240 --> 00:14:46.940
Oh? Hey, guys!

220
00:14:48.940 --> 00:14:52.280
H-Hey, bro. Let's go for a walk.

221
00:14:52.280 --> 00:14:55.650
Just come quietly, and there won't be trouble.

222
00:14:55.650 --> 00:15:00.620
Our captain is very angry.
Give up on living a long life.

223
00:15:01.650 --> 00:15:04.470
What? Are you too scared to talk?

224
00:15:04.470 --> 00:15:07.450
You're Sanji, aren't you?

225
00:15:06.460 --> 00:15:07.470
What?!

226
00:15:07.470 --> 00:15:08.890
So then you're Zoro!

227
00:15:08.890 --> 00:15:12.420
Long time no see, guys!

228
00:15:09.220 --> 00:15:11.380
Wh-Wha...?!

229
00:15:12.430 --> 00:15:15.590
H-Hey, it's been a while! Hasn't it?

230
00:15:15.590 --> 00:15:17.870
Y-Yeah! So let's get going!

231
00:15:17.870 --> 00:15:20.590
Oh, everybody's here already?

232
00:15:20.590 --> 00:15:23.830
Sorry to keep you all waiting!

233
00:15:27.810 --> 00:15:31.210
Do you think he's mistaken us?

234
00:15:31.210 --> 00:15:32.900
Like that really matters!

235
00:15:32.900 --> 00:15:35.120
Let's just get him to the captain!

236
00:15:39.690 --> 00:15:45.130
Straw Hat Rendezvous Point, Grove 46

237
00:15:49.470 --> 00:15:51.630
This is Grove 46.

238
00:15:52.460 --> 00:15:58.170
More and more rookies keep joining
the Straw Hats and showing up here.

239
00:15:58.170 --> 00:16:01.510
I see four captains.

240
00:16:01.510 --> 00:16:04.550
With a bounty of 92 million belly,

241
00:16:01.510 --> 00:16:06.050
Albion "the Maimed"
Bounty:    92 Million

242
00:16:04.550 --> 00:16:06.050
Albion the Maimed.

243
00:16:06.080 --> 00:16:10.790
Lip "Service" Doughty
Bounty:    88 Million

244
00:16:06.920 --> 00:16:08.870
With a bounty of 88 million belly,

245
00:16:08.870 --> 00:16:10.790
Lip "Service" Doughty.

246
00:16:11.980 --> 00:16:15.330
A-And... there are some super rookies...

247
00:16:15.330 --> 00:16:22.570
"Wet-Haired" Caribou
Bounty:    210 Million

248
00:16:15.990 --> 00:16:18.270
The captain of the Caribou Pirates.

249
00:16:18.270 --> 00:16:20.630
With a bounty of 210 million belly,

250
00:16:20.630 --> 00:16:22.570
Wet-Haired Caribou!

251
00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:30.210
"Blood Spatter" Coribou
Bounty:    190 Million

252
00:16:23.260 --> 00:16:25.550
Plus his brother and co-captain.

253
00:16:25.550 --> 00:16:27.980
With a bounty of 190 million belly,

254
00:16:27.980 --> 00:16:30.210
Blood Splatter Coribou!

255
00:16:37.680 --> 00:16:43.790
– Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore!
– Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore!

256
00:16:37.850 --> 00:16:43.790
Sabao Dome
Grove 33

257
00:16:43.790 --> 00:16:49.590
– Encore! Encore! Encore!
– Encore! Encore! Encore!

258
00:16:49.590 --> 00:16:52.650
I see. The Marines, huh?

259
00:16:49.590 --> 00:16:54.560
– Encore! Encore! Encore!
– Encore! Encore! Encore!

260
00:16:53.500 --> 00:16:54.560
I got it.

261
00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:56.500
Don't push!

262
00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:58.740
– Encore! Encore! Encore!
– Encore! Encore! Encore!

263
00:16:56.500 --> 00:16:58.740
Soul King! Come back to us!

264
00:16:58.740 --> 00:17:01.490
I need a little more time.

265
00:16:58.740 --> 00:17:04.710
– Encore! Encore! Encore!
– Encore! Encore! Encore!

266
00:17:01.490 --> 00:17:04.710
Yes... My fans are calling for an encore...

267
00:17:04.710 --> 00:17:09.980
– Encore! Encore! Encore!
– Encore! Encore! Encore!

268
00:17:09.980 --> 00:17:14.520
and since they won't stop,
I have to go back on.
– Encore! Encore! Encore!
– Encore! Encore! Encore!

269
00:17:31.000 --> 00:17:33.940
Thank you for waiting, everybody!

270
00:17:38.910 --> 00:17:42.550
That's it! Show's over!

271
00:17:42.550 --> 00:17:44.750
The Marines are here? But why...?

272
00:17:44.750 --> 00:17:50.250
Acting captain of the Rumbar Pirates:
"Humming Swordsman" Brook!

273
00:17:50.250 --> 00:17:52.760
Bounty: 33 million belly!

274
00:17:52.760 --> 00:17:56.490
We suspect that you are this very pirate!

275
00:17:57.340 --> 00:17:58.920
Furthermore,

276
00:17:58.920 --> 00:18:03.470
intelligence says you're currently
part of Straw Hat Luffy's pirate crew!

277
00:18:03.470 --> 00:18:05.670
Soul King Brook—

278
00:18:05.670 --> 00:18:07.970
rather, Brook the pirate—

279
00:18:07.970 --> 00:18:10.730
you're under arrest!

280
00:18:13.340 --> 00:18:15.680
No way... Our beloved Brook isn't...!

281
00:18:15.680 --> 00:18:17.880
Soul King is a criminal?

282
00:18:17.880 --> 00:18:19.630
He's a pirate?

283
00:18:19.630 --> 00:18:22.690
But I heard Straw Hat Luffy was dead!

284
00:18:23.450 --> 00:18:26.390
It's all over, Brook.

285
00:18:26.390 --> 00:18:29.160
I thought that you might be behind this...

286
00:18:29.820 --> 00:18:31.160
Manager.

287
00:18:31.160 --> 00:18:35.160
When you told me backstage
about your early retirement plans,

288
00:18:35.160 --> 00:18:36.970
you gave me a real shock.

289
00:18:36.970 --> 00:18:42.210
You've become so popular that we were
primed to really rake in the dough.

290
00:18:42.210 --> 00:18:47.880
You've betrayed us, and our agency
will go out of business.

291
00:18:50.380 --> 00:18:54.120
Let's die together, Soul King.

292
00:18:57.250 --> 00:18:59.560
The Sunny's Anchorage, Grove 17

293
00:18:57.790 --> 00:19:00.690
Cool!

294
00:19:00.690 --> 00:19:05.660
Isn't it?! His body is amazing!

295
00:19:13.970 --> 00:19:15.410
You're like a robot!

296
00:19:15.410 --> 00:19:17.910
Can you shoot beams or missiles?!

297
00:19:17.910 --> 00:19:19.910
Can you combine with something?

298
00:19:19.910 --> 00:19:21.210
Naturally!

299
00:19:21.210 --> 00:19:23.810
Shouldering men's passions and dreams

300
00:19:23.810 --> 00:19:26.750
While moving into action is he

301
00:19:26.750 --> 00:19:28.850
The one I call,

302
00:19:34.160 --> 00:19:36.390
Robot! Robot!

303
00:19:36.390 --> 00:19:39.330
Rein it in, Chopper!
This much excitement is deadly!

304
00:19:39.330 --> 00:19:39.360
Rein it in, Chopper!
This much excitement is deadly!

305
00:19:39.360 --> 00:19:39.400
Rein it in, Chopper!
This much excitement is deadly!

306
00:19:39.400 --> 00:19:39.430
Rein it in, Chopper!
This much excitement is deadly!

307
00:19:39.430 --> 00:19:39.460
Rein it in, Chopper!
This much excitement is deadly!

308
00:19:39.460 --> 00:19:39.500
Rein it in, Chopper!
This much excitement is deadly!

309
00:19:39.500 --> 00:19:39.530
Rein it in, Chopper!
This much excitement is deadly!

310
00:19:39.530 --> 00:19:39.560
Rein it in, Chopper!
This much excitement is deadly!

311
00:19:42.780 --> 00:19:47.900
But Franky, you can't do precision work
with those huge hands, can you?

312
00:19:50.470 --> 00:19:51.910
You were saying?

313
00:19:51.910 --> 00:19:54.430
Check it out! A hand!

314
00:19:54.430 --> 00:19:56.110
A hand came out of his hand!

315
00:19:56.110 --> 00:19:58.800
Amazing! Combining!

316
00:19:58.230 --> 00:19:59.480
Robin!

317
00:20:00.620 --> 00:20:01.520
Nami!

318
00:20:02.470 --> 00:20:04.450
You look great!

319
00:20:04.450 --> 00:20:06.490
Combine! Combine!

320
00:20:06.490 --> 00:20:09.790
What's wrong with that weirdo's body?

321
00:20:10.950 --> 00:20:12.960
I don't know, and I don't understand.

322
00:20:14.200 --> 00:20:16.500
Oh, this is the coating?

323
00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:19.440
My nose. Press my nose.

324
00:20:19.440 --> 00:20:20.240
Your nose?

325
00:20:20.240 --> 00:20:23.560
Press and hold it down
for at least three seconds.

326
00:20:24.200 --> 00:20:27.210
Please press the nose
for at least three seconds.

327
00:20:27.210 --> 00:20:29.610
He said it again like a robot!

328
00:20:30.300 --> 00:20:34.680
So exciting... So exciting... So exciting...

329
00:20:32.270 --> 00:20:34.680
One, two, three...

330
00:20:35.890 --> 00:20:37.420
Whoa! Hair!

331
00:20:37.420 --> 00:20:39.930
Hair...!

332
00:20:40.820 --> 00:20:42.290
Can you adjust your hair?

333
00:20:44.230 --> 00:20:45.330
Yes, I can!

334
00:20:45.330 --> 00:20:48.060
– Wow!
– Wow!

335
00:20:48.060 --> 00:20:51.730
Oh, it's Nami! What's up?!

336
00:20:51.730 --> 00:20:53.640
Yeah, hey...

337
00:20:53.640 --> 00:20:56.110
What was he doing for two years?

338
00:20:56.110 --> 00:20:58.880
Can I see your weapons? Can I?!

339
00:21:02.950 --> 00:21:07.550
Hold your horses! That's the main event.
Wait till Luffy gets here too-mecha.

340
00:21:07.550 --> 00:21:09.190
He moved like a robot!

341
00:21:09.190 --> 00:21:11.020
He added "mecha" at the end!

342
00:21:13.950 --> 00:21:14.960
Guys.

343
00:21:16.030 --> 00:21:17.930
Rayleigh! Shakky!

344
00:21:17.930 --> 00:21:21.780
I'm sorry to interrupt your reunion but...

345
00:21:21.780 --> 00:21:25.070
the archipelago is in an uproar right now.

346
00:21:25.070 --> 00:21:26.740
Pirate Brook!

347
00:21:27.260 --> 00:21:31.170
Drop your instrument
and put your hands in the air!

348
00:21:32.410 --> 00:21:33.440
Band.

349
00:21:34.410 --> 00:21:36.580
Backup singers and dancers!

350
00:21:36.580 --> 00:21:40.450
I want you to support me for one more song!

351
00:21:44.420 --> 00:21:46.320
Don't worry!

352
00:21:46.320 --> 00:21:49.030
My music's got power now!

353
00:21:49.890 --> 00:21:51.830
Are you insane?

354
00:21:51.830 --> 00:21:54.030
It's all over for you, Brook.

355
00:21:54.030 --> 00:21:58.000
Manager, thank you for everything
these past two years.

356
00:21:59.470 --> 00:22:02.970
And thank you for bringing me
to this archipelago.

357
00:22:03.810 --> 00:22:09.190
This island holds the sad memory
of our crushing defeat...

358
00:22:09.190 --> 00:22:11.310
but it's where we'll begin anew!

359
00:22:12.410 --> 00:22:14.120
I'm a musician.

360
00:22:14.120 --> 00:22:19.190
My role on the Straw Hat crew is to make
the adventure a little more lively.

361
00:22:20.040 --> 00:22:23.250
People think Straw Hat Luffy is dead?

362
00:22:23.250 --> 00:22:24.510
That's nonsense!

363
00:22:25.460 --> 00:22:28.100
Tell this to the whole world:

364
00:22:28.100 --> 00:22:31.530
The pirate Straw Hat Luffy...

365
00:22:31.530 --> 00:22:34.200
is alive!

366
00:22:37.710 --> 00:22:41.610
He'll be the one to conquer
the world's seas someday!

367
00:22:41.610 --> 00:22:45.310
Main office...? Can you hear me?
It's news...! Big news!

368
00:22:45.310 --> 00:22:50.990
His departure shouldn't
be a quiet one! Oh, baby!

369
00:22:52.590 --> 00:22:54.020
Soul King...!

370
00:22:54.020 --> 00:22:56.830
Love me down to the bone!

371
00:22:56.830 --> 00:23:03.470
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

372
00:23:00.370 --> 00:23:03.470
This song is dedicated to my dear friends.

373
00:23:03.470 --> 00:23:07.040
Listen to this, my ultimate soul!

374
00:23:07.040 --> 00:23:08.800
Yeah!

375
00:23:08.800 --> 00:23:12.110
Luffy, let's go to the New World!

376
00:23:12.110 --> 00:23:14.680
You numbskull! I said the show is ov–

377
00:23:14.680 --> 00:23:15.810
Shove it, Marines!

378
00:23:18.280 --> 00:23:20.650
Let us hear one more song!

379
00:23:20.650 --> 00:23:22.150
Let him sing!

380
00:23:22.150 --> 00:23:25.760
Yeah, let him! All that matters
to us is that he's the Soul King!

381
00:23:26.470 --> 00:23:29.690
See? Music is always on your side!

382
00:23:32.260 --> 00:23:33.900
One, two, three, four...

383
00:23:36.170 --> 00:23:37.830
"New World"!

384
00:23:42.870 --> 00:23:47.040
Grove 46, Sabaody Archipelago

385
00:23:44.670 --> 00:23:47.040
This is Grove 46.

386
00:23:47.140 --> 00:23:51.550
Straw Hat Rendezvous Point

387
00:23:47.870 --> 00:23:51.550
There're at least a hundred pirates here now.

388
00:23:54.120 --> 00:23:58.590
If they've all joined Straw Hat Luffy's crew,
then this is a real emer–

389
00:24:03.190 --> 00:24:05.330
Hey, what's wrong?! Answer!

390
00:24:08.000 --> 00:24:10.200
Not good! Tell the reinforcements to hurry!

391
00:24:11.630 --> 00:24:14.570
Well, well, well...

392
00:24:14.570 --> 00:24:19.480
I had my suspicions, but if it isn't a Marine!

393
00:24:19.480 --> 00:24:21.940
Oh my, oh my!

394
00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:25.350
And what do we have here?

395
00:24:29.840 --> 00:24:34.570
Oh! Oh! Don't tell me...

396
00:24:35.730 --> 00:24:40.660
Were you just informing the Marines?

397
00:24:42.130 --> 00:24:43.760
Is that so?

398
00:24:44.370 --> 00:24:46.440
He's a Marine.

399
00:24:46.440 --> 00:24:48.900
N-No, I haven't called them yet!

400
00:24:48.900 --> 00:24:50.670
I was just about to...

401
00:24:50.670 --> 00:24:55.240
Oh, not that. Don't even think about it.

402
00:24:55.240 --> 00:25:00.070
Otherwise, blood will get everywhere...

403
00:25:00.070 --> 00:25:03.520
The blood of you and your friends!

404
00:25:03.520 --> 00:25:06.360
Isn't that right, Coribou?

405
00:25:06.360 --> 00:25:09.730
Huh?! I'm sorry, brother, I'm so sorry!

406
00:25:09.730 --> 00:25:13.330
I'm over here, you fool!

407
00:25:14.490 --> 00:25:16.070
I'm sorry!

408
00:25:16.070 --> 00:25:17.470
Still the wrong way,

409
00:25:17.470 --> 00:25:20.200
you dim-witted simpleton!

410
00:25:20.200 --> 00:25:22.640
Marine Slayer Caribou...

411
00:25:48.300 --> 00:25:51.830
Enough jokes.

412
00:25:51.830 --> 00:25:53.300
He did it!

413
00:25:53.300 --> 00:25:54.700
True to his reputation...

414
00:25:56.670 --> 00:26:01.980
Oh, God! Have mercy!

415
00:26:01.980 --> 00:26:08.220
This silly little Marine reached for
his weapon and attempted to kill me!

416
00:26:08.220 --> 00:26:11.420
Please have mercy on him!

417
00:26:11.420 --> 00:26:14.890
I'm sorry, God! So sorry!

418
00:26:16.010 --> 00:26:18.330
Bury him, Coribou!

419
00:26:18.330 --> 00:26:23.430
This Marine is a sinful man...
and must be buried alive!

420
00:26:23.430 --> 00:26:24.200
Okay!

421
00:26:24.200 --> 00:26:26.060
Gotta dig, gotta dig...

422
00:26:26.060 --> 00:26:29.870
W-W-Wait a minute! Don't do this!

423
00:26:26.060 --> 00:26:31.870
I'm diggin' a hole, just diggin it up...

424
00:26:29.870 --> 00:26:31.870
I never called the Marines...!

425
00:26:31.870 --> 00:26:33.810
That's enough, Caribou!

426
00:26:34.870 --> 00:26:36.150
Oh?

427
00:26:36.150 --> 00:26:41.620
Just dispose of that pissant
Marine somewhere.

428
00:26:42.890 --> 00:26:45.820
Here comes Captain Straw Hat Luffy!

429
00:26:47.890 --> 00:26:50.890
You guys, look around you!

430
00:26:50.890 --> 00:26:55.490
You probably don't know each other,
but all of you work for me now...

431
00:26:56.400 --> 00:26:59.240
as a part of the Straw Hat crew!

432
00:27:02.140 --> 00:27:05.910
That means when I become
King of the Pirates,

433
00:27:05.910 --> 00:27:08.110
that'll make you the Pirate King's crew!

434
00:27:09.650 --> 00:27:12.010
In order to make that happen,

435
00:27:12.010 --> 00:27:17.490
you'll need to commit both body and soul
and risk your life for me in battle!

436
00:27:19.160 --> 00:27:23.190
It's like a dream! He's taken on all three
strongholds of the World Government,

437
00:27:23.190 --> 00:27:27.030
Enies Lobby, Impel Down,
and Marine Headquarters!

438
00:27:27.030 --> 00:27:33.240
You'd be lucky to serve
under such a peerless pirate!

439
00:27:33.240 --> 00:27:37.870
He'll be a strong candidate
for King of the Pirates!

440
00:27:37.870 --> 00:27:40.210
Might as well jump on the bandwagon!

441
00:27:43.970 --> 00:27:46.620
Wow, looks like quite the turnout.

442
00:27:46.620 --> 00:27:48.220
Is that it?

443
00:27:48.220 --> 00:27:50.850
I can't wait to see everybody!

444
00:27:55.560 --> 00:27:57.860
Shut up!

445
00:27:59.730 --> 00:28:03.830
We asked you to assemble here because...

446
00:28:03.830 --> 00:28:09.970
I, your beloved boss,
have had my honor tarnished!

447
00:28:13.740 --> 00:28:17.010
Those responsible are
somewhere on this archipelago!

448
00:28:17.010 --> 00:28:21.480
I need you to track them down
and drag them here!

449
00:28:22.500 --> 00:28:24.850
Consider it done, Boss!

450
00:28:24.850 --> 00:28:27.260
I won't forgive those fools!

451
00:28:29.020 --> 00:28:31.960
Say, two years can really change a person.

452
00:28:32.790 --> 00:28:34.730
You guys don't talk much now, do you?

453
00:28:35.660 --> 00:28:40.940
Looks like this guy with the mustache
does know the real Straw Hats.

454
00:28:40.940 --> 00:28:42.440
Who is he?

455
00:28:42.440 --> 00:28:46.310
Beats me, but he'll notice if we talk too much.

456
00:28:46.310 --> 00:28:49.670
All we gotta do is take him to the captain.

457
00:28:49.670 --> 00:28:50.410
Okay.

458
00:28:50.410 --> 00:28:53.780
Y'know, you two were never
this friendly with each other...

459
00:28:55.680 --> 00:28:57.520
Well, it's been two years after all.

460
00:28:59.290 --> 00:29:01.290
You look different too.

461
00:29:01.290 --> 00:29:02.630
Are you also in disguise?

462
00:29:08.030 --> 00:29:10.670
Hey, wait!

463
00:29:10.670 --> 00:29:12.400
The Marines?

464
00:29:12.400 --> 00:29:19.110
Yes, they think those impostors are actually
little Monkey's crew and are mobilizing.

465
00:29:19.110 --> 00:29:22.850
I had them wiretapped, so there's no mistake.

466
00:29:22.850 --> 00:29:28.480
I spoke to Brook through a transponder snail
and told him what's going on.

467
00:29:28.480 --> 00:29:30.790
He should be heading this way soon.

468
00:29:30.790 --> 00:29:34.160
Oh, so he's gonna abandon stardom?

469
00:29:34.160 --> 00:29:36.730
That backbone of his isn't just for show.

470
00:29:36.730 --> 00:29:39.700
Nami, you're the navigator, correct?

471
00:29:39.700 --> 00:29:43.580
I'll teach you how to operate
the coated ship, so listen carefully.

472
00:29:43.580 --> 00:29:44.300
Okay.

473
00:29:45.100 --> 00:29:46.240
I'll do my best!

474
00:29:46.240 --> 00:29:48.270
Oh, what's this?

475
00:29:48.270 --> 00:29:50.170
It's all tense and stuff now.

476
00:29:50.170 --> 00:29:53.680
But, Rayleigh, Luffy isn't here yet!

477
00:29:53.680 --> 00:29:55.040
Don't worry!

478
00:29:55.040 --> 00:29:57.050
Captain!

479
00:29:57.050 --> 00:29:57.710
Huh?

480
00:29:57.710 --> 00:30:00.220
That's "big boss" to you, dumbass!

481
00:30:00.220 --> 00:30:07.560
We couldn't find their old pet,
but isn't this the guy you were looking for?

482
00:30:08.860 --> 00:30:10.060
Ah...

483
00:30:10.790 --> 00:30:14.060
Luffy has already arrived.

484
00:30:18.170 --> 00:30:19.440
I can't wait!

485
00:30:19.440 --> 00:30:23.910
I gave Sanji a baby transponder snail
when he stopped by earlier.

486
00:30:23.910 --> 00:30:25.410
He's with Zoro now.

487
00:30:25.410 --> 00:30:27.640
Oh, that's good.

488
00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:32.010
You guys have to hurry—
the Marines will be here soon.

489
00:30:32.010 --> 00:30:35.950
It's only our little Monkey that we can't reach.

490
00:30:35.950 --> 00:30:39.460
But your crew should
keep this vivre card on you.

491
00:30:39.460 --> 00:30:41.820
It'll lead him right to you.

492
00:30:41.820 --> 00:30:45.530
Grove 42 is right by the sea,
making it the perfect place.

493
00:30:45.530 --> 00:30:48.460
Sail on over there for your rendezvous!

494
00:30:49.200 --> 00:30:53.170
It's a little hectic, but after you
all got through these two years...

495
00:30:54.240 --> 00:30:56.940
it's finally time for a new beginning!
